  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n*Summary*: I was connected to WiFi router but the router temporary did not have internet connection. The app showed \"Offline\" status but when I sent messages, their status was \"Sent\". When device got back online, I checked the other device but messages were not delivered.  \r\n\r\nA message that was marked as \"Sent\" while being offline (connected to WiFi but without internet):\r\n<img src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/7532782/40783622-54f5d01c-64e3-11e8-975e-58c8207340b5.png\" width=\"200\">\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nThere should be spinner indicating that the messages are trying to be sent. After timeout, the messages should be marked as not sent.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nThe messages were incorrectly marked as sent.\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n- Open Status\r\n- Connect to WiFi without internet connection\r\n- Status shows Offline\r\n- Send a message\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: nightly, May 31\r\n* Operating System: tested only on Android",
